We requested No peppers, and when the pizza came...it was LOADED with peppers. Waitress ordered a new pie for us. When it came the outside crust was crispy, but the rest was soggy and greasy. Disappointing. The diet coke was flat. The ambience was nice, but pizza is nothing to write home about. Save your money and purchase a Tombstone pizza from the grocery store.

I had high hopes for this restaurant based on reviews. The hostess was welcoming. The atmosphere depends on which side of the restaurant you get seated at (it's better in the south side room). The server made me feel I was in a basic pizza joint the way the salad and garlic bread were just "tossed" onto the table. Salad was bland and uses a lot of iceberg lettuce. The toasted garlic parmesan bread was very tasty. The baked meat lasagna was outstanding. An Italian sausage patty is baked into the lasagna as a layer. The entire dish is generously covered in a delicious marinara sause and smothered mozzarella. The fettuccini carbonara was fresh and richly creamy. Overall a very good dining experience.

We wanted authentic Italian so we were excited. The restaurant makes it seem like it is. I ordered the chicken compamare and my husband had the coco Maria pizza. I had a tough time ordering because I couldn't make sense of the menu. It sounded like weird concoctions (for the pasta). So I finally threw a dart at one.lol.  First they brought out bread sticks which it wasn't. It was french bread disguised as garlic bread. Wasn't good, it was pretty amateur. I also had a salad which was decent. I like it this way (oil and vinegar as the dressing) this is the way my mother  and grandmother made salads. Then our meals came pretty quickly. This always worries me when restaurants do this because then I wonder if it is truly homemade/made to order?  My chicken compamare was not a filet but small pieces (reminds me of frozen strips in a bag at the store). Then the noodles were spaghetti not fettuccine.  The sauce wasn't bad. The other ingredients just were not the star of the dish. My husband liked his pizza. I then ask for the dessert menu and the waitress told me the items. I then asked if they are made fresh/homemade?  No, they get them from Chicago. So disappointing but at least she was honest. Didn't order a dessert.  Staff were nice , atmosphere nice but I expected better. They don't have parm or pepper flakes at the table, you have to ask. All Italians like pepper flakes to accentuate their pasta.  Unfortunately if we are back in the area, we won't be back.

Had lunch midafternoon on a Saturday. I ordered chicken milanese and the wife had a father Giovanni's pizza.  My meal came with family style salad and garlic bread. So after the lightly dressed salad and garlic bread with too much dry parm like you'd shake out of a can, I get my entree which is unseasoned spaghetti on the bottom covered by a breaded chicken breast topped by a massive amount of greens with the same or similar salad dressing.  Like having a salad followed by a salad.  This dish clearly doesn't work.  The greens were quite bitter and the balsamic salad dressing that soaked down on to the spaghetti at the bottom wasn't an appealing taste.  I ate the breast and left the rest.  The wife's pizza which was supposed to be topped with tomatoes,  fresh mozzarella,  and basil was actually sauce, shredded mozzarella,  and no visible fresh basil.  If you've ever had a frozen Jack's or Roma pizza you'd be in the ballpark even though the comparison is unfair to cheap frozen pizzas. Crust was like a Carr's Water Cracker.  How this place rates highly is beyond me.

When the waitress came around and asked how it was I told her it was incredibly spicy and she just looked at me like I was an idiot and told me “Well yeah, it has hot sauce in it.” I’m not sure if I mistakenly ordered the wrong dish or why I didn’t expect the heat, but nonetheless it’s spiciness was much to high for me to enjoy. While I understand adding hot sauce to a cream sauce or marinara, this was quite literally linguine tossed in hot sauce. I paid and left most of my food on the table. I will not be reccomending this location to my family or friends, nor will I be returning. The one positive note was the same addicting garlic bread from the Galena location.

I don't even know where to begin. This has been the best eating experience of my life. From walking in the door to leaving it was just perfect. The building is an old brick kind of Italian feel with real family photos on the walls,checkered table clothes,a beautiful full bar,different levels,hand carved wood and old Italian decor. Just a very lovely feel and very romantic ( we went for a mother's day date). The music was wonderful and quiet enough for good conversation too. Wait staff was friendly,smiling and very attentive. The food came almost immediately and was very hot and fresh. For an Italian place the Calamari is excellent. Servings are large and taste homemade. I even enjoyed the oil and vinegar vinegrette on the salad which i usually am not too fond of. The  high point of our meal was when the owner came over and talked to us and made sure everything was good. Several wait staff stopped to chat too which gave it a real family feel. The prices are reasonable as well. The whole experience was really much better than a 5 star rating,but unfortunately that's as high as it goes on here. I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone. We will be coming back again anytime we are close.

Came here for lunch the other day on a recommendation. Love! Loved the old building and the decorations inside, the old ceiling. The food was ahhhmazing! I usually don't like vinagrette on salad but theirs is really good. Garlic bread to die for. I got the special of the day, eggplant parmesan. Really really good. I'm getting hungry just thinking about it. I'm not from Dubuque, I was a driver for Hirschbach so I'm not sure if I'll ever be back which is unfortunate. Edit: I almost forgot about the tiramisu I got to go. OMG. Best tiramisu I've ever had.

Service was very good. The food mediocre. We went as a large group and they had the dinners out in the dining area before the group even got in the building...some people got cold food. Overall NOT a bad experience. The desserts are excellent!
Sucked
Great food
Great location. Italian sized portions, authentic ingredients. Menu was a bit limited, but fitting for the venue. Service was great, good spot for families.
This is the first time I went there but definitely not the last time. Food was great as well as the starters. Specially garlic bread! Would highly recommend for Italian food.
Food was excellent, atmosphere was very nice, service suffered, due to being short handed.
Great American Italian food
No black olives available. Great service.
Great food. Price reasonable. Good service.

Wonderful food, atmosphere and service! Close to downtown Dubuque 4th Street Elevator and little shops as well as the National Mississippi River Museum & Aquarium!
Way too much greese
Awesome meal with enjoyable staff.
Great place to eat!
Not authentic Italian.  Unimpressed except for good wine list.
Great place for a date night out. Lots of good food. Decent bar  in there as well.

My favorite thing was the salad.  My main meal, not trying to sound mean, tasted like a frozen healthy choice meal.  I think it was the chicken, just had the texture of those meals. I'm willing to go back and try again.  Maybe I just went there on a bad day?
Good food and service. Drinks took a long time to get with each order/refill.

Was recommended to this place by some girls at the Hotel Julien Bar. They raved about it so we were pretty excited. Atmosphere was nice and so was our waiter. However the garlic bread was nothing magical like everyone has been saying. It was super dry and the parm on top made it so I had to drink my water to get it down. The house salad was yummy. We ordered the lasagna and ravioli. Really let down with how average it was for the prices we paid. $20 a plate and it’s the same quality as the frozen Italian food we buy and cook. It also took a really long time to get our food and there was only two other couples there. I definitely wouldn’t go back.
Mediocre food for the price.
Really good food and great outing for a offive team dinner. The ambience is quiet and the staff is friendly.
This is high on my list of favorite restaurants!
Best Italian food around
Amazing food! Especially their bread!
It's ok but prefer Marios for Italian food
Great food

I hate to give this place only two stars, since the food was about 4-5 stars. Yet, the service was so terrible I can't give it more than 2 stars. It was so dark in there we had to turn on our cell phones to see the menu. (We were sat at the very back table on the 2nd floor). The ice water we were given was in a very small glass, and we were thirsty. Our waiter only re-filled our glasses once, while we sat there thirsty most of the time.  He would disappear for very long stretches of time, leaving us hanging. My husband ordered a beer, which never even came, yet we were still charged for it. The waiter said "Oh, they never brought up your beer?" Well, he should have checked with us to make sure we got it. He was so inattentive. The food was excellent, but was so disappointed in the service or lack thereof, that we will not be back.
Loved the garlic bread, the service and the atmosphere.  I ordered Vinny's a la pasta and was very pleased.  Will definitely return and highly recommend this restaurant to others.
Awesome staff & atmosphere, cozy too.  The food is superb, love it here!  The brushetta appitizer is really really good.

We visited on a weekday evening during what looked like a staff meeting. Our waitress was slow getting to us and after we ordered pre-dinner cocktails, it was a long wait to get our drinks. The food was good and we would have ordered desserts, but she brought our bill and never asked us if we wanted anything else. So, thumbs up for the food, thumbs down for the service.

My only regret how about Vinny's is I am old and it's a lot of food to eat. The food has always been great. The staff friendly and efficient. My only disappointment is they discontinued the family style special for four people. We used to be able to get bunch of stuff at a reasonable price which we always enjoy. Regular menu is not overpriced has great selections and the food is outstanding. Servers have always been friendly efficient and eager to please.
Great food and great service. Just wish they had sangria Year round
This is a great little restaurant a hidden gem.
Great place..Great Food.. Great atmosphere! However don't go on a cold day. Draft and not much heat
The best service anywhere.  Great food reasonable prices
Absolutely fine food. Family atmosphere. And very helpfful wait staff
Always delicious and good service!

Absolutely fantastic Italian food ran by an Italian family.  The way it should be made.  With love and compassion.  Excellent wait staff. That went above and beyond. Will definitely be back. Costly, or higher prices. But well worth the money. Had a fantastic time with my husband, my daughter, & my two grandchildren (girls).
A true Taste of Italy and a little Midwestern town. Vinny's reputation lives on.

Since I moved to Dubuque I have been visiting this place atleast once a month. I took my mom for dinner today. I ordered for an appetizer and entree pasta dish. I asked for a plate to split this food between me and my mom(I asked for nothing extra from the basic portion that was served and I mean even the salad or bread).  I was told I would be charged for a plate. I said I had asked for nothing more but yet if you say so then go ahead charge me. Later on she came back and told me the owner says its fine but from next time you would be charged for a plate. we lost our appetite in this did not even finish our food and left.
By far my favorite restaurant in Dubuque. Exceptional food and service

Food is consistently good here and the decor is lovely. Service is always friendly. It's a Dubuque staple and I hope they never close.

Salad is beyond compare. Appreciate the gluten free menu items, but my entree was too heavily spiced for my palate. Server was very attentive, and it's a fine atmosphere for relaxing and catching up with a friend I haven't seen in a long time.
